Hyperparameter Optimization¶

In [571]:
from hyperopt import fmin, tpe, hp, STATUS_OK, Trials
In [578]:
#this is very time consuming, more than 12h

def auc_model(params):
    clf_2 = GradientBoostingClassifier(**params).fit(X_PCA_train,y_train)
    return roc_auc_score(y_train, clf_2.predict_proba(X_PCA_train)[:, 1])
   

param_space = {
    'max_depth': hp.choice('max_depth', range(1,30)),
    'n_estimators': hp.choice('n_estimators', range(100,500)),
    'learning_rate': hp.loguniform('learning_rate', np.log(0.005), np.log(0.7))}


best = 0
def f(params):
    global best
    auc = auc_model(params)
    if auc > best:
        best = auc
    print ('new best:', best, params)
    return {'loss': -auc, 'status': STATUS_OK}

trials = Trials()
best = fmin(f, param_space, algo=tpe.suggest, max_evals=50, trials=trials)
print ('best:')
print (best)

#much faster 15 min

def auc_model(params):
    clf_2 = GradientBoostingClassifier(**params) 
    CV_resul= cross_validate(clf_2, X_PCA_train, y_train, cv=3, scoring=('roc_auc'), return_train_score=False, n_jobs= -1)
    return CV_resul['test_score'].max()

param_space = {
    'max_depth': hp.choice('max_depth', range(1,10)),
    'n_estimators': hp.choice('n_estimators', range(50,250)),
    'learning_rate': hp.loguniform('learning_rate', np.log(0.05), np.log(0.5))}


best = 0
def f(params):
    global best
    auc = auc_model(params)
    if auc > best:
        best = auc
    print ('new best:', best, params)
    return {'loss': -auc, 'status': STATUS_OK}

trials = Trials()
best = fmin(f, param_space, algo=tpe.suggest, max_evals=10, trials=trials)
print ('best:')
print (best)
